{
  "texts": [
    "REM stage refers to the time spent in REM sleep.",
    "Sleep latency refers to the sum of the time of SLL sleep latency, N2 latency time, and N3 latency time.",
    "Sleep efficiency is calculated as the ratio of the time of sleep to the time of being in bed.",
    "Sleep duration refers to the number of awakenings, ratio of total awakening time to total sleep time.",
    "Sleep Structure: (a) SLL Latency Time; (b) Sleep Latency Time; (c) N1 Latency Time; (d) N2 Latency Time; (e) REM Latency Time; (f) Non-rapid Eye Sleep (N1%, N2%, N3%, and REM%) as a percentage of total sleep time."
  ]
}